"Zhihui Xiaoxiang" 2021 China International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry Talent Summit Opens - Rolling News - Hunan Daily Network - Huasheng Online Hunan Daily December 10th News (All-media reporter Zhou Zhongheng) On the 9th, the "Zhihui Xiaoxiang" 2021 China International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry Talent Summit opened in Zhuzhou. Wang Cheng, a member of the Standing Committee of the Provincial Party Committee and Minister of the Organization Department of the Provincial Party Committee, attended the launching ceremony and delivered a speech. Wang Cheng pointed out that holding the talent summit is an important measure to implement the spirit of the Central Talent Work Conference and the 12th Provincial Party Congress. It demonstrates Hunan's sincerity in valuing talents, desiring talents, and making good use of talents. Hunan has a fine tradition of recognizing, loving, and respecting talents, a broad platform to help talents develop, and environmental conditions to realize a better life. In recent years, it has deeply implemented the talent-led development strategy, driven by the Furong Talent Action Plan, and built a complete talent work pattern of attracting, cultivating, and retaining talents, making it a fertile ground for talent growth and achievements, a hotbed for innovation and entrepreneurship, and a land suitable for living and working. At present, Hunan is comprehensively implementing the "three highs and four news" strategic positioning and mission tasks, and will further open the door to attract and recruit talents, providing better policies, concentrating more resources, and creating better conditions for talent innovation and entrepreneurship. It is expected that outstanding talents from all walks of life will gather their wisdom and contribute to the high-quality development of Hunan. At the event site, Changsha, Zhuzhou, Xiangtan pavilions and Hunan Free Trade Zone pavilions were set up. The provincial departments of Science and Technology, Industry and Information Technology, and Human Resources and Social Affairs released a list of key demands for scientific and technological innovation in advanced manufacturing-related industries, a catalog of talent needs for the intelligent manufacturing industry, and a catalog of youth talent needs for the intelligent manufacturing industry in post-doctoral mobile stations. Forty-eight large enterprises, including China CRRC, Zoomlion, and Broad Group, recruited talents on-site, and nearly a thousand fresh graduates and professionals in relevant fields participated in the talent project matchmaking.
